{
  "summary": "The document is the Universities (Amendment) Act, No. 7 of 1985, which amends the Universities Act, No. 16 of 1978. The amendments involve changes to the composition and powers of the University Grants Commission, regulations regarding University Councils and Senates, and other administrative and financial aspects of higher education in Sri Lanka.",
  "referenced_acts": [
    "Universities Act, No. 16 of 1978",
    "Employees' Provident Fund Act, No. 15 of 1958",
    "Trusts Ordinance",
    "Administration of Justice Law, No. 44 of 1973",
    "University of Ceylon Act, No. 1 of 1972",
    "Higher Education Act, No. 20 of 1966",
    "Government Quarters (Recovery of Possession) Act, No. 7 of 1969",
    "State Industrial Corporations Act, No. 49 of 1957",
    "State Lands (Recovery of Possession) Act, No. 7 ot 1979",
    "Bribery Act",
    "Penal Code"
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "section_number": "1",
      "content": "This Act may be cited as the Universities (Amendment) Act, No. 7 of 1935, and shall come into operation in respect of all or any of its provisions on such date or dates as the Minister may appoint by Order published in the Gazette.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Short title and date of operation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "2",
      "content": "Section 4 of the Universities Act, No. 16 of 1978 (hereinafter referred to as the \"principal enactment\") is hereby amended by the repeal of subsection (1) of that section and the substitution therefor, of the following subsection:\n\n\"(1) The Commission shall consist of a Chairman, a Vice-Chairman and five other members, all of whom shall be appointed by the President.\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 4 of Act No. 16 of 1978."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3",
      "content": "Section 5 of the principal enactment is hereby amended as follows:\n(1) by the substitution, in subsection (1) of that section, for the words \"including the Chairman, shall\", of the words \"including the Chairman and the Vice-Chairman, shall, \";\n(2) by the substitution, in subsection (3) of that section-\n(a) for the words \"If the Chairman, on other\", of the words \"If the Chairman, Vice-Chairman, or other\", and\n(b) for the words \"such Chairman, or a fit person\", of the words \"such Chtirman or Vice-Chairman, or a fit person\"; and\n(3) by the substiution, in subsection (4) of that section, for the words \"The Chairman and other members\", of the words \"The Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other members\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 5 of the principal enactment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4",
      "content": "Section 6 of the principal enactment is hereby amended by the repeal of subsections (1) and (2) of that section and the substitution therefor, of the following subsections :-\n\n\"(1) The Chairman of the Commission shall preside at all meetings of the Commission. In the absence of the Chairman from any meeting of the Commission, the Vice-Chairman shall preside at such meeting.\"",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 6 of the principal enactment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "5",
      "content": "Section 7 of the principal enactment is hereby amended as follows:-\n(1) by the repeal of subsection (1) of that section and the substitution therefor, of the following subsection:-\n\n\"(1) The Cuirman shall be the chief executive officer and the Accounting Officer of the Commission.\";\n(2) by the substitution, in subsection (3) of that section, for the expression \"under sections 15, 16 and 18\", of the expression \"under sections 16 and 18\".;\n(3) by the substitution, in subsection (4) of that section, for the words \"the Camirman shall be subject\" of the words \"the Chairman and the Vice-Chairman shall be subject\"; and\n(4) by the substitution, for the marginal note to that section, of the following marginal note :-\n\"Chairman and Vice-Chairman of the Commission. \".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 7 of the principal enactment,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "6",
      "content": "Section 8 of the principal enactment is hereby amended as follows:-\n(1) by the substitution, for paragraph (a) of subsection (1) of that section, of the following paragraph :-\n\"(a) a Secretary, who shall be responsible for the custody of the records and the property of the Commission, and shall also be the Assistant Accounting Officer of the Commission; and\";\n(2) by the remumbering of subsection (2) of that section as subsection (3) thereof ; and\n(3) by the insertion, immediately after subsection (1) of that section, of the following new subsection:-\n\n(2) The provisions of sections 74 and 75, shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to and in relation to the officers and employees of the Commission, other than those officers and employees appointed to the staff of the Commission under the provisions of subsection (5) of section 9.\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 8 of the principal enactment"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "7",
      "content": "Section 9 of the principal enactment is hereby amended in subsection (5) of that section, as follows :-\n(1) by the substitution, for the words \"any officer or other employee\", of the words \"any teacher, officer or other employee\"; and\n(2) by the substitution, for the words \"that officer or employee\", of the words \"that teacher, officer or employee\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 9 of the principal enactment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "9A",
      "content": "Every holder of a post in the Commission who is dismissed or is compulsorily retired from his post or is othersiwe punished for misconduct, inefficiency or dereliction of duty, may appeal against such dismissal or retirement or other punishment to the Univer sity Services Appeals Board.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Appeal against dismissal, compulsory retirement or other punishment, by holder of post in Commission."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "9B",
      "content": "(1) The seal of the Commission shall be in the custody of the Secretary of the Commission.\n(2) The seal of the Commission may be altered in such manner as may be determined by the Commission.\n(3) The seal of the Commission shall not be affixed to any instrument or document except in the presence of the Secretary and any member of the commission, both of whom shall sign the instrument or document in token of their presence.\"",
      "footnotes": [
        "Seal of the Commission."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "15",
      "content": "Section 29 of the principal enactment is hereby amended in paragraph (1) of that section, by the substitution, for the words \"to institure Professorships\", of the words \"to recommend to the Commission the institution of Professorships\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 29 of the principal enactment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "17",
      "content": "Section 34 of the principal enactment is hereby amended as follows:\n(1) by the repeal of subsection (1) of that section and the substitution therefor, of the following subsection:-\n(1) (a) The Vice-Chancellor of a University shall be appointed for a term of three years by the President upon the recommendation of the Commission from a panel of three names recommended by the Council of that University.\n(b) The Vice-Chancellor of a University may be removed from office by the President, after consultation with the Commission.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 34 of the principal enactment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "45",
      "content": "Section 86 of the principal enactment is hereby amended as follows: \n(1) by the substitution, in paragraph (b) of that section, for the words \"otherwise punished against,\" of the words \"otherwise punished for misconduct, inefficiency or dereliction of duty, against \"; and\n(2) by the substitution, in paragraph (d) of that section, for the words \"Commission or the governing authority of the Higher\", of the words \"Commission or the principal executive officer of the Higher\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 86 of the principal enactment."
      ]
    }
  ],
  "amendments": [
    {
      "type": "Repeal",
      "description": "Repeals section 41, 42 and 43 of the principal enactment."
    },
    {
      "type": "Repeal",
      "description": "Repeals section 134 of the principal enactment."
    },
    {
      "type": "Repeal",
      "description": "Repeals section 113 of the principal enactment."
    },
    {
      "type": "Substitution",
      "description": "Substitutes new language related to the membership of the Commission",
      "section": "2"
    }
  ],
  "entities": [
    {
      "entity_name": "President",
      "entity_type": "Person",
      "excerpt": "all of whom shall be appointed by the President"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Minister",
      "entity_type": "Person",
      "excerpt": "as the Minister may appoint by Order published in the Gazette"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "University Grants Commission",
      "entity_type": "Other",
      "excerpt": "Commission from among persons who have rendered distinguished service"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Secretary",
      "entity_type": "Other",
      "excerpt": "in the custody of the Secretary of the Commission"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "University Services Appeals Board",
      "entity_type": "Other",
      "excerpt": "may appeal against such dismissal or retirement or other punishment to the Univer sity Services Appeals Board"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Ministry of the Minister",
      "entity_type": "Ministry",
      "excerpt": "by the consent of that officer, the Secretary to the Ministry"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Local Government",
