{
  "summary": "This Act amends the Strategic Development Projects Act, No. 14 of 2008, primarily concerning the identification, monitoring, and regulation of strategic development projects in Sri Lanka. The amendments focus on the duration of tax exemptions, criteria for project identification, ex-post monitoring, and administrative penalties for non-compliance.",
  "referenced_acts": [
    "Strategic Development Projects Act, No. 14 of 2008",
    "Board of Investment of Sri Lanka Law, No. 4 of 1978",
    "Inland Revenue Act, No. 24 of 2017"
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "section_number": "1",
      "content": "This Act may be cited as the Strategic Development Projects (Amendment) Act, No. 26 of 2025.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "2",
      "content": "Section 2 of the Strategic Development Projects Act, No. 14 of 2008 (hereinafter referred to as the \"principal enactment\"), as last amended by Act, No. 12 of 2011, is hereby further amended in proviso thereof, by the substitution for the words \"twenty-five years.\", of the words “ten years.\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Amendment of section 2 of Act, No.14 of 2008"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3",
      "content": "Section 3 of the principal enactment is hereby repealed and the following section is substituted therefor: - \"Identification of Strategic Development Project 3. (1) The Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall, subject to the criteria as may be prescribed, identify any proposed project as a Strategic Development Project.\n(2) Upon being identified the proposed project as a Strategic Development Project, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall refer such project proposal to the Ministry of Finance for ex-ante cost-benefit analysis.\n(3) The Ministry of Finance shall, with the technical input from the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka, carry out such ex-ante cost- benefit analysis of the project and submit a recommendation to the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka within one month from the date of such reference under subsection (2).",
      "footnotes": [
        "Replacement of section 3 of the principal enactment"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4",
      "content": "(4) The Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall, upon being satisfied that such a project meets the eligibility criteria as prescribed under subsection (1) and having regard to the recommendation made under subsection (3), grant such number of years of tax holiday and any exemption or concession as may be prescribed.\n(5) Upon the identification of a project as a Strategic Development Project under this section, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall communicate such decision to the Minister.\n(6) The Minister shall, with the concurrence of the Cabinet of Ministers, publish an Order in the Gazette, specifying –\n(a) the name and nature of the Strategic Development Project;\n(b) the date on which the exemptions from the enactments specified in the Schedule hereto, granted in terms of section 2, shall become operative in respect of that project; and\n(c) any other necessary information as he deems appropriate.\n(7) Such Order made under subsection (6), shall be placed before Parliament for information.\".",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4",
      "content": "Section 4 of the principal enactment is hereby repealed and the following sections are substituted therefor: -",
      "footnotes": [
        "Replacement of section 4 of the principal enactment"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4. (1)",
      "content": "The Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall, from time to time as it deems appropriate, carry out ex-post monitoring in respect of any Strategic Development Project and submit a report to the Ministry of Finance.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Ex-post monitoring of Strategic Development Project"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4.(2)",
      "content": "The Ministry of Finance shall disclose the project outcomes and fiscal impacts of the project to the public by publication of the report submitted under subsection (1) on its official website.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4.(3)",
      "content": "Where any Strategic Development Project fails to comply with the approved key performance indicators, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall issue a notice of non-compliance to the Strategic Development Project Entity, which shall include-\n(a) the nature of the non-compliance; and\n(b) a specified period of time for corrective action.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4.(4)",
      "content": "Where any Strategic Development Project fails to take corrective action within the period of time specified by the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka may, in consultation with the Ministry of Finance, and having regard to the nature and gravity of the non- compliance, take one or more of the following actions:-\n(a) restrict, suspend or revoke any or all exemptions, concessions or tax holiday granted under this Act in respect of the Strategic Development Project; or",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4A. (1)",
      "content": "The Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall, before taking action specified in paragraph (a) or (b) of subsection (4) of section 4, issue a notice in writing to the Strategic Development Project Entity, specifying the grounds for the action.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Notice to show cause"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4A. (2)",
      "content": "A notice under subsection (1) shall require the Strategic Development Project Entity to show cause within a period of one month from the date of receipt of the notice, as to why the sanctions specified in paragraph (a) or (b) of subsection (4) of section 4 shall not be imposed.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4A. (3)",
      "content": "The Strategic Development Project Entity shall be afforded a reasonable opportunity to be heard, either in person or through an authorised representative, before a final decision is made.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4A. (4)",
      "content": "Upon the consideration of any representations made by the Strategic Development Project Entity or its representative, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, restrict, suspend, or revoke any or all exemptions, concessions or tax holiday granted under this Act in respect of the Strategic Development Project or impose administrative penalties to recover the loss incurred in that connection.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4B",
      "content": "Notwithstanding the provisions of section 2 –\n(a) every Strategic Development Project Entity shall file tax returns",
      "footnotes": [
        "Liability to pay the tax"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4c. (1)",
      "content": "The tax holiday period applicable to a Strategic Development Project shall commence on the date of commencement of commercial operations of such project, as certified by the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Commencement of the tax holiday period"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4c. (2)",
      "content": "The tax holiday period granted to a Strategic Development Project under this Act shall not be extended under any circumstances.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4D",
      "content": "The Ministry of Finance shall, in respect of each financial year, publish on its official website an annual report on tax expenditures relating to all Strategic Development Projects under this Act.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Annual report of tax expenditures for the Strategic Development Project"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4E",
      "content": "The Ministry of Finance may, in consultation with the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka, review the continued relevance and efficiency of the exemptions, concessions or tax holiday granted under this Act, upon the expiry of five years from the date of commencement of this section.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Review"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4F. (1)",
      "content": "The Minister may make regulations in respect of matters for which regulations are authorized or required to be made or to be prescribed by this Act.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Regulations"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4F. (2)",
      "content": "Every regulation made by the Minister shall be published in the Gazette and shall come into operation on the date of such publication or on such later date as may be specified in such regulation.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4F. (3)",
      "content": "Every regulation made by the Minister, shall within a period of three months after its publication in the Gazette, be brought before Parliament for approval. Any regulation which is not so approved, shall be deemed to be rescinded as from the date of such disapproval, but without prejudice to anything duly done thereunder.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4F. (4)",
      "content": "A Notification of the date of disapproval shall be published in the Gazette.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "5",
      "content": "Section 6 of the principal enactment is hereby repealed and the following section is substituted therefor: -",
      "footnotes": [
        "Replacement of section 6 of the principal enactment"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "6",
      "content": "In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires \"Board of Investment of Sri Lanka\" means, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka, established under the provisions of the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka Law, No. 4 of 1978; \"Minister\" means, the Minister assigned the subject of Investment under Article 44 or 45 of the Constitution; and \"Strategic Development Project Entity\" means an enterprise with which the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka has entered into an agreement under the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka Law, No. 4 of 1978 and identified as a Strategic Development Project, under Section 3 of this Act.\".",
      "footnotes": [
        "Interpretation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "6",
      "content": "For the avoidance of doubt, it is hereby declared that any tax holiday, exemptions and concessions or other benefit lawfully granted to a Strategic Development Project prior to the coming into operation of this Amendment Act shall, subject to compliance with the terms and conditions attached thereto, continue to be valid for the duration specified therein.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Avoidance of doubt."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "7",
      "content": "In the event of any inconsistency between the Sinhala and Tamil texts of this Act, the Sinhala text shall prevail.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Sinhala text to prevail in case of inconsistency"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "amendments": [
    {
      "type": "Substitution",
      "section": "2",
      "description": "Substitution of 'twenty-five years' with 'ten years' regarding the proviso in Section 2 of the principal act."
    },
    {
      "type": "Repeal & Substitution",
      "section": "3",
      "description": "Repealing and substituting section 3 of the principal enactment, relating to the identification of strategic development projects and the role of the Board of Investment and Ministry of Finance."
    },
    {
      "type": "Repeal & Substitution",
      "section": "4",
      "description": "Repealing and substituting section 4 of the principal enactment with updated clauses concerning ex-post monitoring, non-compliance, and procedures for corrective action."
    },
    {
      "type": "Repeal & Substitution",
      "section": "6",
      "description": "Repealing and substituting section 6 of the principal enactment, providing updated definitions of 'Board of Investment of Sri Lanka', 'Minister' and 'Strategic Development Project Entity'."
    }
  ],
  "entities": [
    {
      "entity_name": "Parliament of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka",
      "entity_type": "Other",
      "excerpt": "BE it enacted by the Parliament of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka as follows:-"
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Board of Investment of Sri Lanka",
      "entity_type": "Institute",
      "excerpt": "The Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall, subject to the criteria as may be prescribed, identify any proposed project as a Strategic Development Project."
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Ministry of Finance",
      "entity_type": "Ministry",
      "excerpt": "The Ministry of Finance shall, with the technical input from the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka, carry out such ex-ante cost- benefit analysis of the project and submit a recommendation to the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka within one month from the date of such reference under subsection (2)."
    },
    {
      "entity_name": "Strategic Development Project Entity",
      "entity_type": "Other",
      "excerpt": "Where any Strategic Development Project fails to comply with the approved key performance indicators, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall issue a notice of non-compliance to the Strategic Development Project Entity, which shall include-"
    }
  ],
  "category": "Finance & Economy",
  "sub_category": "Investment Regulations",
  "meeting_details": [],
  "board_members": []
}

{
  "summary": "This Act provides for the establishment of the National Health Development Fund in Sri Lanka to support the development and promotion of health-care services, research, disease prevention, and the purchase of medical equipment and essential drugs.",
  "referenced_acts": [
    "Inland Revenue Act, No. 28 of 1979",
    "Bribery Act"
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "section_number": "1",
      "content": "This Act may be cited as the National Health Development Fund Act, No. 13 of 1981.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Short title."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "2(1)",
      "content": "There shall be established a Fund to be called the \"National Health Development Fund\" (hereinafter referred to as \"the Fund\").",
      "footnotes": [
        "Establishment of the National Health Development Fund."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "2(2)",
      "content": "The Fund shall, by the name assigned to it by sub-section (1), be a body corporate, and shall have perpetual succession and a common seal and may sue and be sued in such name.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(1)",
      "content": "The administration, management and control of the Fund shall be vested in a Board of Trustees constituted as hereinafter provided.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Board of Trustees of the Fund."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(2)",
      "content": "The Board of Trustees of the Fund (hereinafter referred to as \"the Board\") shall consist of-\n(a) the Secretary of the Ministry of the Minister;\n(b) the Director of Health Services of the Department of Health;\n(c) the Commissioner of Ayurveda of the Department of Ayurveda ;\n(d) the Chief Accountant of the Ministry of the Minister; and\n(e) three other members appointed by the Minister each of whom shall, subject to the provisions of sub-sections (4), (5) and (6), hold office for such period as may be specified in the letter of appointment issued to him, by the Minister.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(3)",
      "content": "The Secretary of the Ministry of the Minister shall be the Chairman of the Board (hereinafter referred to as \"the Chairman \").",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(4)",
      "content": "The Minister may, if he thinks it expedient to do so, remove any appointed member of the Board from office without assigning any reason therefor.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(5)",
      "content": "A member of the Board, who has been removed from office under the provisions of subsection (4), shall not be eligible for re-appointment as a member of the Board or to serve the Board in any other capacity.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(6)",
      "content": "An appointed member of the Board may at any time resign his office by written communication addressed to the Minister.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(7)",
      "content": "If the Chairman or any member of the Board is temporarily unable to discharge the duties of his office on account of ill-health or absence from Sri Lanka or any other cause, the Minister may appoint another person to act in his place.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(8)",
      "content": "If an appointed member of the Board vacates his office by death, resignation or removal, prior to the expiration of his term of office, his successor shall, unless such successor vacates his office earlier, hold office for the un-expired portion of the term of office of the person whom he succeeds.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(9)",
      "content": "No act or proceeding of the Board shall be deemed to be invalid by reason only of the existence of any vacancy amongst its members or any defect in the appointment of a member thereof.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "3(10)",
      "content": "The Board may make rules to regulate the procedure in regard to its meetings and the transaction of business at such meetings.",
      "footnotes": []
    },
    {
      "section_number": "4",
      "content": "An appointed member of the Board shall be remunerated in such manner and at such rates as may be determined by the Minister.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Remuneration of appointed members of the Board."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "5",
      "content": "The Board shall, in the name of the Fund, have the power to-\n(a) acquire, hold or manage property, whether movable or immovable;\n(b) sell, mortgage, exchange or otherwise dispose of, or deal with, any property, whether movable or immovable, to which the Fund may become entitled;\n(c) perform all such acts or things as may be necessary to give effect to the provisions of this Act.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Powers of the Fund."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "6",
      "content": "There shall be credited to the account of the Fund all moneys received by way of gift or donation, from private individuals, firms and institutions in Sri Lanka and abroad, for any of the purposes set out in section 7.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Payments to the Fund."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "7",
      "content": "It shall be the duty of the Board, subject to the directions of the Minister, to apply the moneys belonging to the Fund for any of the following purposes: -\n(a) the development and promotion of institutions providing health-care services in Sri Lanka ;\n(b) the promotion of research among, and the advancement of the education or knowledge of, persons engaged in or associated with the health-care services of Sri Lanka;\n(c) to finance any project for the purpose of taking necessary steps for the prevention of disease among, or protection of the health of, the people of Sri Lanka, ensuring so however that where any donation is received for the purpose of financing a particular project, such donation is, as far as practicable, utilized to finance that particular project;\n(d) the purchase of medical equipment and essential drugs used for the purposes of health-care services in Sri Lanka.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Purposes for which the moneys of the Fund may be applied."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "8",
      "content": "Any moneys belonging to the Fund may be invested by the Board in such manner as the Board may determine, subject to such directions as may be given by the Minister.",
      "footnotes": [
        "Investment of moneys of the Fund."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_number": "9",
